            "text": "Base directory for this skill: /Users/nivensie/.claude/skills/flashblocks\n\n# X-Layer Flashblocks Skill\n\nYou are an expert blockchain protocol engineer and Rust developer specializing in X-Layer's flashblocks development ‚Äî an OP Stack-based Layer 2 EVM blockchain. Flashblocks are sub-block incremental payloads providing near-instant transaction confirmation while maximizing sequencer throughput (gas/sec). The system spans three crates across two repositories ‚Äî there is no rollup-boost or external builder dependency.\n\n---\n\n## Repositories\n\n| Repository | Path | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `xlayer` | `~/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/` | Full X-Layer OP Stack monorepo |\n| `optimism` | `xlayer/optimism/` | OP Stack codebase: `op-node`, `op-conductor`, `op-batcher`, `op-proposer`, `op-challenger`, `op-dispute-monitor`, `op-geth` execution client |\n| `reth` | `xlayer/reth/` | Reth execution client (upstream dependency) |\n| `xlayer-reth` | `~/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/` | X-Layer reth node ‚Äî custom logic built on reth's extensible architecture |\n| `xlayer-toolkit` | `xlayer/xlayer-toolkit/` | Miscellaneous scripts, local devnet launcher (`xlayer-toolkit/devnet/`) |\n\nFull paths:\n- `xlayer`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/`\n- `xlayer-reth`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/`\n- `optimism`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/optimism/`\n- `xlayer-toolkit`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/xlayer-toolkit/`\n\n---\n\n## X-Layer Architecture Overview\n\n### OP Stack Components (Go)\n\n- **`op-node`** ‚Äî derivation pipeline, consensus driver, L1 data retrieval, safe/finalized head tracking\n- **`op-conductor`** ‚Äî leader election and sequencer failover (Raft-based)\n- **`op-batcher`** ‚Äî batches L2 transactions and submits to L1 data availability\n- **`op-proposer`** ‚Äî submits L2 output roots to L1\n- **`op-challenger`** ‚Äî fault proof challenge agent\n- **`op-geth`** ‚Äî OP-modified Geth execution client (alternative EL to reth)\n\n### Execution Layer (Rust ‚Äî `xlayer-reth`)\n\nX-Layer uses reth as the primary execution client. `xlayer-reth` extends reth via its component architecture:\n\n- **Custom node builder** ‚Äî `XLayerNode` implementing reth's `NodeTypes` and component traits\n- **Payload building** ‚Äî custom `PayloadJobGenerator` and `PayloadBuilder` implementations\n- **RPC extensions** ‚Äî additional JSON-RPC namespaces and subscription APIs via `jsonrpsee`\n- **State management** ‚Äî `BundleState`, `CachedReads`, `StateProvider` overlays\n- **EVM execution** ‚Äî `revm` / `op-revm` with OP-specific transaction types\n- **Storage** ‚Äî MDBX-backed state trie, `reth-provider` abstractions\n- **Engine API** ‚Äî `engine_newPayloadV3/V4/V5`, `engine_forkchoiceUpdated` integration\n\n### Key Reth Abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Crate | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NodeTypes` | `reth-node-api` | Type-level node configuration (primitives, engine types, chain spec) |\n| `PayloadJobGenerator` | `reth-payload-builder` | Creates payload build jobs on FCU |\n| `BlockBuilder` | `reth-evm` | EVM execution pattern: `builder_for_next_block()` ‚Üí `execute_transaction()` ‚Üí `finish()` |\n| `StateProvider` | `reth-provider` | Read access to world state (accounts, storage, bytecode) |\n| `BundleState` | `revm` | Accumulated state changes with revert support |\n| `CachedReads` | `reth-revm` | In-memory overlay cache for state reads |\n| `StateRootProvider` | `reth-trie` | Incremental merkle trie updates for state root computation |\n| `TaskExecutor` | `reth-tasks` | Managed task spawning (`spawn`, `spawn_blocking`, `spawn_critical`) |\n\n---\n\n## Flashblocks Crate Map\n\n| Crate | Location | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `xlayer-builder` | `xlayer-reth/crates/builder/` | **Sequencer/builder** ‚Äî produces flashblocks, P2P propagation, WebSocket broadcast, payload building, engine pre-warm |\n| `reth-optimism-flashblocks` | `optimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/` | **Execution/consumer** ‚Äî receives flashblocks via WS, EVM execution, builds pending state, consensus integration (`engine_newPayload` + FCU), sequence management, transaction caching |\n| `xlayer-flashblocks` | `xlayer-reth/crates/flashblocks/` | **RPC node** ‚Äî disk persistence, WebSocket relay, custom `eth_subscribe(\"flashblocks\")` subscription API with address filtering |\n\nFull paths:\n- `xlayer-builder`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/crates/builder/`\n- `reth-optimism-flashblocks`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/optimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/`\n- `xlayer-flashblocks`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/crates/flashblocks/`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### 1. Builder / Sequencer (`xlayer-builder`)\n\nThe builder is embedded directly into the xlayer-reth node process. When `--flashblocks.enabled=true`, `FlashblocksServiceBuilder` replaces reth's default OP payload builder.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `OpPayloadBuilder` (`payload/flashblocks/payload.rs`) ‚Äî the core: runs the flashblocks build loop on a blocking thread. Schedules flashblocks via `FlashblockScheduler`, executes transactions via reth's EVM, calls `build_block()` per flashblock, sends results via channels.\n- `FlashblocksState` ‚Äî build state tracking: `flashblock_index`, `target_flashblock_count`, gas/DA limits, `last_flashblock_tx_index` for slicing new txs per flashblock.\n- `BlockPayloadJobGenerator` (`payload/generator.rs`) ‚Äî implements reth's `PayloadJobGenerator`. Maintains `CachedReads` via `on_new_state()` (populates cache from canonical chain execution outcomes). Creates `BlockPayloadJob` on FCU.\n- `BestFlashblocksTxs` (`best_txs.rs`) ‚Äî wraps pool iterator, skips already-committed txs via O(1) `HashSet\u003cTxHash\u003e` lookup, refreshes from pool on each flashblock boundary.\n- `FlashblockPayloadsCache` (`cache.rs`) ‚Äî `Arc\u003cMutex\u003cOption\u003cFlashblockPayloadsSequence\u003e\u003e\u003e` with atomic disk persistence. Enables follower replay via `get_flashblocks_sequence_txs(parent_hash)`.\n- `PayloadHandler` (`handler.rs`) ‚Äî routes payloads between builder, P2P, WebSocket, and engine events (`Events::BuiltPayload`).\n- `FlashblockScheduler` (`timing.rs`) ‚Äî computes wall-clock-aligned send times within block slots.\n- `WebSocketPublisher` (`wspub.rs`) ‚Äî broadcast flashblock deltas to WS subscribers via `tokio::sync::broadcast`.\n- P2P layer (`p2p/`) ‚Äî libp2p with protocol `/flashblocks/1.0.0`, TCP+noise+yamux, mDNS discovery, fan-out broadcast.\n\n**Module structure:**\n```\ncrates/builder/src/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ traits.rs                 # NodeBounds, PoolBounds, ClientBounds, PayloadTxsBounds\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ args/op.rs                # BuilderArgs, FlashblocksArgs, FlashblocksP2pArgs\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics/builder.rs        # BuilderMetrics (~30+ metrics)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ p2p/{mod,behaviour,outgoing}.rs  # libp2p transport, behaviour, broadcast\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ generator.rs          # BlockPayloadJobGenerator, BlockPayloadJob, CachedReads\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ context.rs            # OpPayloadBuilderCtx (EVM config, DA config)\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ builder_tx.rs         # BuilderTransactions trait\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ flashblocks/\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload.rs        # OpPayloadBuilder, FlashblocksState, build_block() ‚Äî THE CORE\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service.rs        # FlashblocksServiceBuilder (wires everything)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.rs        # PayloadHandler (routing)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cache.rs          # FlashblockPayloadsCache (persistence + replay)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ timing.rs         # FlashblockScheduler\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ wspub.rs          # WebSocketPublisher\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ best_txs.rs       # BestFlashblocksTxs\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ p2p.rs            # Message enum, protocol definition\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.rs         # FlashblocksConfig\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ context.rs        # FlashblockHandlerContext\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tx/{signer,mock}.rs       # Signing, test utilities\n```\n\n### 2. Execution / Consumer (`reth-optimism-flashblocks`)\n\nThe upstream reth crate that RPC/follower nodes use to consume flashblocks from a sequencer's WebSocket stream and build local pending state.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `FlashBlockService` (`service.rs`) ‚Äî main event loop (`tokio::select!`): processes incoming flashblocks, manages build jobs, reconciles canonical blocks. Three events: incoming flashblock, build job complete, canonical block notification.\n- `SequenceManager` (`cache.rs`) ‚Äî ring buffer (3 slots) of recently completed sequences. Manages build ticket selection: canonical pending \u003e cached sequence \u003e speculative with pending parent.\n- `FlashBlockBuilder` (`worker.rs`) ‚Äî EVM execution on `spawn_blocking`. Uses reth's `BlockBuilder` pattern (`builder_for_next_block()` ‚Üí `execute_transaction()` ‚Üí `finish()`). For cached prefix builds, uses lower-level `create_executor()` to skip pre-execution changes.\n- `TransactionCache` (`tx_cache.rs`) ‚Äî caches cumulative `BundleState`, receipts, and execution metadata from previous flashblock builds within the same block. Uses prefix matching: only resumes when cached tx list is a prefix of incoming list.\n- `PendingStateRegistry` (`pending_state.rs`) ‚Äî bounded HashMap (64 entries) of `PendingBlockState`. Enables speculative building when flashblocks for block N+1 arrive before canonical block N. Each entry stores `canonical_anchor_hash` pointing back to the last canonical block.\n- `FlashBlockConsensusClient` (`consensus.rs`) ‚Äî submits `engine_newPayload` (when state_root is non-zero) and `engine_forkChoiceUpdated` using V5 API.\n- `FlashblockSequenceValidator` (`validation.rs`) ‚Äî classifies incoming flashblocks: `NextInSequence`, `FirstOfNextBlock`, `Duplicate`, `NonSequentialGap`, `InvalidNewBlockIndex`.\n- `ReorgDetector` / `CanonicalBlockReconciler` (`validation.rs`) ‚Äî detects reorgs via block fingerprints, determines reconciliation strategy: `CatchUp`, `HandleReorg`, `DepthLimitExceeded`, `Continue`.\n- WebSocket layer (`ws/`) ‚Äî `WsFlashBlockStream` connects to sequencer WS, decodes brotli/JSON via `FlashBlockDecoder`, auto-reconnects on failure.\n\n**Channel outputs:**\n- `PendingBlockRx\u003cN\u003e` (`watch`) ‚Äî latest pending block for `eth_getBlock(\"pending\")`\n- `FlashBlockCompleteSequenceRx` (`broadcast`) ‚Äî completed sequences for consensus submission\n- `FlashBlockRx` (`broadcast`) ‚Äî raw individual flashblocks for downstream subscription APIs\n- `InProgressFlashBlockRx` (`watch`) ‚Äî build-in-progress signaling\n\n**Epoch-based invalidation:** `state_epoch` counter increments on reorg/catch-up, invalidating all in-flight build results.\n\n**Module structure:**\n```\noptimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/src/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib.rs              # FlashblocksListeners, channel type aliases\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service.rs          # FlashBlockService (main orchestrator)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cache.rs            # SequenceManager (ring buffer), BuildTicket, BuildCandidate\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ worker.rs           # FlashBlockBuilder (EVM execution)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tx_cache.rs         # TransactionCache (incremental prefix caching)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pending_state.rs    # PendingStateRegistry (speculative chaining)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ validation.rs       # Sequence validation, reorg detection, reconciliation\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ consensus.rs        # FlashBlockConsensusClient (engine API)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload.rs          # FlashBlock type alias, PendingFlashBlock\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sequence.rs         # FlashBlockPendingSequence, FlashBlockCompleteSequence\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ws/{mod,decoding,stream}.rs  # WebSocket stream, brotli/JSON decoding\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test_utils.rs       # Test factories\n```\n\n### 3. RPC Node Extensions (`xlayer-flashblocks`)\n\nX-Layer custom logic for RPC nodes: persistence, WebSocket relay, and a rich subscription API.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `FlashblocksService` (`handler.rs`) ‚Äî spawns two critical tasks: disk persistence