- `metadata: OpFlashblockPayloadMetadata` ‚Äî `receipts` (by tx hash), `new_account_balances`, `block_number`\n\n---\n\n## State Root Computation (Builder ‚Äî Three Modes)\n\n1. **Per-flashblock sync** (`disable_state_root = false`): Each flashblock calls `build_block(calculate_state_root=true)`. Inline: `state.merge_transitions()` ‚Üí `hashed_post_state()` ‚Üí `state_root_with_updates()`. Transition state is saved/restored for incremental builds.\n\n2. **Disabled per-flashblock** (`disable_state_root = true`): Flashblocks emit `state_root = B256::ZERO`. Only the fallback payload (index 0) computes state root.\n\n3. **Async on resolution** (`disable_async_calculate_state_root = false`): On `getPayload`, if best payload has zero state root, `resolve_zero_state_root` spawns on a blocking thread. Returns fallback payload immediately; async result pre-warms engine tree via `Events::BuiltPayload`.\n\n**Consumer side**: `FlashBlockConsensusClient` submits `engine_newPayload` only when `state_root != B256::ZERO`. FCU is always sent.\n\n**Rule**: State root MUST be computed before committing to the engine tree. Never delegate to an external EL.\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimization Areas\n\n### 1. Sequencer Throughput (Gas/Second)\n\nGoal: Maximize gas processed per second on the sequencer.\n\nKey levers:\n- **Single canonical state** ‚Äî builder writes directly into the node's state provider, no cross-EL sync\n- **Engine cache hits** ‚Äî `Events::BuiltPayload` pre-warms engine tree so `engine_newPayload` is a cache hit, not re-execution\n- **`CachedReads` overlay** ‚Äî `on_new_state()` populates cache from canonical chain outcomes; EVM uses `cached_reads.as_db_mut(state_provider_db)`\n- **Transaction iteration** ‚Äî `BestFlashblocksTxs` skips committed txs via O(1) hash lookup, refreshes from pool per flashblock\n- **Flashblock scheduling** ‚Äî `FlashblockScheduler` aligns to wall-clock slots; configurable cadence (default 250ms), offset, end-buffer\n- **Follower catch-up** ‚Äî `FlashblockPayloadsCache` enables transaction replay on failover\n\nTarget: `engine_cache_hit_rate \u003e 99%`, `engine_newPayload` p50 \u003c 50ms, p95 \u003c 250ms\n\n### 2. Execution Speed (Reth Alignment)\n\nGoal: Transaction execution never blocks the async event loop.\n\nKey design:\n- **Blocking thread isolation** ‚Äî `OpPayloadBuilder::try_build()` runs on `spawn_blocking` (builder); `FlashBlockBuilder` uses `TaskExecutor::spawn_blocking()` (consumer)\n- **Reth EVM path** ‚Äî standard `evm.transact()` with `CachedReads` overlay (builder); `BlockBuilder` pattern with `execute_transaction()` (consumer)\n- **Incremental state** ‚Äî `BundleState` with `BundleRetention::Reverts` allows incremental flashblock builds; transition state snapshotted/restored between flashblocks (builder)\n- **Transaction prefix caching** ‚Äî `TransactionCache` provides warm `BundleState` prestate for prefix reuse within a block, avoiding redundant execution (consumer)\n- **DA-aware execution** ‚Äî per-tx DA size check (`OpDAConfig`) prevents DA overflow mid-flashblock\n\n### 3. State Trie \u0026 Merklization Speed (Reth Alignment)\n\nGoal: Minimize state root computation latency.\n\nKey design:\n- **`state_root_with_updates(hashed_state)`** ‚Äî uses `reth_trie` for incremental merkle trie updates via `StateRootProvider`\n- **`hashed_post_state(\u0026bundle_state)`** ‚Äî only hashes modified accounts/storage, not full state\n- **Transition save/restore** ‚Äî `merge_transitions` + restore avoids re-merging the full bundle on each flashblock\n- **Async resolution** ‚Äî state root computed on separate blocking thread while fallback payload returned immediately\n- **Engine pre-warm with trie data** ‚Äî async state root sends `BuiltPayload` event with `hashed_state` and `trie_updates` so engine tree applies them directly\n- **Consumer-side auto state root** ‚Äî triggered near expected final flashblock index (based on `block_time`)\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Flashblock